 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Director of Engineering Alldus New York, NY Director of Engineering - Security Products - leading a growing team (currently 6 soon to be 30) 
 We're an industry leading Security platform using machine learning and artificial intelligence to baseline communication content, user identity, and behavioral signals in real-time and at-scale in order to detect the abnormalities of email attacks. 
 Our veteran team has built some of the most enduring machine learning platforms at leading companies including Google, Twitter, Pinterest, Amazon, Microsoft, and Expanse. We are located in San Francisco and New York City. 
 Our company is growing - we’re on the  Forbes AI 50 , and a  Gartner 2020 Cool Vendor , and our customer base includes multiple Fortune 500 companies. 
 Job Responsibilities 
 Lead multiple engineering teams with different responsibilities: 
 Lead team of  Product Engineers  building next-gen email security products 
 Frontend Engineers responsible for building all customer-facing web applications 
 “Customer fast track” engineering team, building customer delighting features to accelerate & close strategic sales deals 
 Go-To-Market (Sales, Customer Success, & Marketing) Eng support team, whose charter is to improve their GTM team’s efficacy and velocity 
 Product Development 
 Work closely with Product Management to ingest new product requirements from customers 
 Manage & be accountable for project delivery execution & output 
 Management 
 Be able to manage both IC engineers, as well as train & manage line level EMs 
 Set clear performance management goals for all team members, and coach them for maximum growth potential 
 Create processes & org structures to improve org engineering capabilities 
 Hiring 
 Demonstrated track record of hiring world class engineers who will thrive in a fast growth startup environment 
 Set and fulfill recruiting plan - creating job descriptions, hiring guides, sourcing, screening, & interviewing candidates 
 X-team support 
 Work closely with partners & stakeholders across the company (Engineering, Product, Customer Success, Sales, Marketing, etc.) 
 Frontend 
 Build a new common UX design system and UI Component library in collaboration with design teams ensuring consistency and coherence across all products 
 Experience / background 
 Enterprise SaaS / Cybersecurity background a big plus 
 Your Experience 
 Experience leading full stack & backend engineering teams 
 Plus if there is experience with ML products 
 Experience with developing and bringing to market enterprise products 
 Someone who has been through the experience of building teams from 5 -> 50 
 Ability to manage both ICs and managers 
 Ability to develop organizational execution capabilities - not the single force 
 Strong coach & recruiting magnet 
 Hire A+ talent in a repeatable, reliable way 
 Has seen excellence - been part of a world-class organization before 
